        r read
        w write
        x exectue

A file contains with 3 sections of permissions
      
      user(owner) => u
      group => g
      others => o


`chmod u+x f1.txt`  →  add execute (x) permission to user (owner)

`chmod u-w f1.txt`  →  remove write (w) permission from user (owner)

`chmod g+wx f1.txt`  →  add write (w) and execute (x) permissions to group

`chmod 000 f1.txt`  →  remove all permissions (no read, write, execute)

`chmod 456 f1.txt`  →  set permissions:

* user = read (4)
* group = read + execute (5)
* others = read + write (6)



chown john f1.txt → change owner of file to user john

sudo chown :devopsgrp f1.txt → change group of file to devopsgrp

chown new-owner:new-group file/directory → change both owner and group



